395
00:29:33,560 --> 00:29:37,560
We can't point any fingers,
not even at Mrs. Deagle.

396
00:29:38,400 --> 00:29:41,560
She's been threatening him.
She'd love to get her hands on him.

397
00:29:41,760 --> 00:29:46,680
We don't have proof. We can't even
find footprints leading up to the house.

398
00:29:48,120 --> 00:29:51,240
I'm gonna take Barney
to your grandmother's.

399
00:29:51,480 --> 00:29:54,840
Take him there on the way to the
convention, pick him up on the way home.

400
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:58,560
He'll be here for Christmas.
It'll be all right.

401
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:05,960
I don't think we can drink this.

402
00:30:10,520 --> 00:30:11,960
Why not?

403
00:30:12,400 --> 00:30:13,960
What's wrong with this?

404
00:30:23,400 --> 00:30:24,960
Is that a mogwai.

405
00:30:25,160 --> 00:30:28,000
Yeah, I'm gonna have
Mr. Hanson check it out.

406
00:30:28,200 --> 00:30:31,760
And all of a sudden, there were
five new ones like this one.

407
00:30:33,360 --> 00:30:34,960
Now watch this.

408
00:31:10,680 --> 00:31:14,000
Can I keep one of these here,
run some tests on him?

409
00:31:15,240 --> 00:31:17,040
I think I can spare one.

410
00:31:25,960 --> 00:31:28,640
This is some Christmas, Katie,
I'll tell you.

411
00:31:28,840 --> 00:31:33,680
First the old bat closes the factory,
and now it's my goddamn plow.

412
00:31:33,880 --> 00:31:36,800
Mr. Futterman, guess what?
It's time to go home now.

413
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:39,160
- How about one more beer?
- No, it's late.

414
00:31:39,360 --> 00:31:41,200
One more beer,
I'll help you clean up.

415
00:31:41,400 --> 00:31:44,000
No, thanks, though.
It'll be okay.

416
00:31:46,800 --> 00:31:49,240
- It'll be okay.
- It will not be okay.

417
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:53,440
I brought my plow in for a tune-up
and found it loaded with foreign parts.

418
00:31:53,800 --> 00:31:56,840
I mean, everything.
Gaskets, pistons, spark plugs.

419
00:31:57,080 --> 00:31:58,800
All of it's foreign.

420
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:04,400
Going home?

421
00:32:09,880 --> 00:32:11,120
Gremlins!

422
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:14,400
You gotta watch out for foreigners.

423
00:32:14,640 --> 00:32:16,840
They plant gremlins
in their machinery.

424
00:32:17,040 --> 00:32:20,720
The same gremlins brought down
our planes in the big one.

425
00:32:21,440 --> 00:32:22,840
That's right.

426
00:32:23,080 --> 00:32:24,520
World War II.

427
00:32:24,720 --> 00:32:25,680
Good old...

428
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:28,200
...W- W-l-I.

429
00:32:31,960 --> 00:32:34,400
They're still shipping them over here.

430
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:36,400
They put them in the cars, the TV.

431
00:32:36,600 --> 00:32:39,240
They put them in the radios
you stick in your ears.

432
00:32:39,480 --> 00:32:42,200
They put them in the watches.
Little teeny gremlins.

433
00:32:42,440 --> 00:32:45,760
It's not a good idea that you drive.
Why don't you walk home?

434
00:32:46,360 --> 00:32:49,040
You know, Katie, I think
maybe I'll walk home.

435
00:32:49,280 --> 00:32:50,080
Good.

436
00:32:50,280 --> 00:32:52,200
It's a nice night.

437
00:32:56,160 --> 00:32:57,600
Good night, kids.

438
00:33:00,680 --> 00:33:02,200
Gremlins.

439
00:33:27,680 --> 00:33:31,080
That was really good,
the way you handled Mr. Futterman.

440
00:33:31,440 --> 00:33:33,000
I'm used to it.

441
00:33:33,480 --> 00:33:36,200
He's been like that
ever since he lost his job.

442
00:33:37,040 --> 00:33:41,360
He's like a lot of people around here.
He just wants somebody to listen.

443
00:33:41,560 --> 00:33:43,400
Especially around the holidays.

444
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:45,880
Why is that?

445
00:33:46,080 --> 00:33:48,800
It's when a lot of people
get really depressed.

446
00:33:50,080 --> 00:33:54,560
I always thought everyone was happy
during the holidays, no matter what.

447
00:33:54,760 --> 00:33:57,280
Most people are, but some aren't.

448
00:33:57,480 --> 00:34:01,440
